SIMPLE: would
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Would
<hw>Would</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>imp.</pos> of <er>Will</er>. <ety>[OE.
& AS. <ets>wolde</ets>. See <er>Will</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>
<def>Commonly used as an auxiliary verb, either in the past tense or in
the conditional or optative present. See 2d & 3d
<er>Will</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Would</xex> was formerly used also as the past
participle of <er>Will</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Right as our Lord hath <qex>would</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Would</ent>⟦br⟧

